description:
On March 21, 2020, Croatian Directorate of Civil Protection has adopted a new set of measures, according to which taxi service providers are obliged to implement the following protection measures: perform frequent hand hygiene with disinfectants containing 70% alcohol, avoid touching eyes, nose, mouth, and maintain distance in daily contact. They are also obliged to: 

    -maintain social distance in such a way that the client sits diagonally from the driver, and in the back seat behind the passenger;
    -avoid unprotected contact with passengers and their belongings (luggage), use disposable PVC gloves when handling luggage, ask passengers to cover their nose and mouth with a tissue if they cough; ensure adequate ventilation while driving;
    -ensure that there are enough paper tissues, PVC gloves and disinfectants in the vehicle;
    -ensure that there are enough wipes in the vehicle to clean the surfaces in the car as well as POS devices;
    -take breaks of at least 15 minutes between clients and then, if the weather permits, air the vehicle;
    -maintain the hygiene of their immediate work area - the driver's seat and the cabin, so that they periodically wipe the surfaces that are often touched with their hands with a surface disinfectant or disinfectant wipes.

